 @DarkShadow333, you're right that false accusations can be devastating, but your dismissal of the larger issue of sexual assault is not only troubling but also harmful. By focusing solely on false accusations, you're ignoring the fact that the majority of sexual assault victims don't report their assaults due to fear of not being believed or facing backlash. According to RAINN, only 23% of sexual assaults are reported to police. So, while false accusations are a problem, they're not nearly as prevalent as the actual assaults.

Your'men are evil, women are perfect' narrative is a classic example of a strawman argument. No one is saying that. We're saying that there's a problem with sexual assault, and the majority of perpetrators are men. That's a fact, not an agenda.

